To calibrate and validate the classification, 1000 points were randomly generated for each study area and visually identified as having flower presence or not (
 Figure 
  3
 ). This is a common practice in Remote Sensing when very high resolution images are available and the distinction between the classes is clear (
 Feng et al., 2015; 
 Lehmann et al., 2017; 
 Müllerová et al., 2017b) as it is in our case (
 A. longifolia flowers vs. everything else, 
 Supplementary Figure 
  S9
 ).
